<anchor xml:id="__options_8h_1a46d23885cbf2bcb255f7e7598c1e6158"/><section>
    <title>DIM_TIME</title>
<indexterm><primary>DIM_TIME</primary><secondary>Options.h</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Options.h</primary><secondary>DIM_TIME</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>constexpr uint16_t DIM_TIME = 5 * 1000<computeroutput>[constexpr]</computeroutput></computeroutput></para>
<para>Time (ms) after waking up that the display will dim and the volume indicator will go away. </para>
</section>
<anchor xml:id="__options_8h_1a15fbe001b7b77c9f6a0236f855861541"/><section>
    <title>MAXIMUM_VOLUME</title>
<indexterm><primary>MAXIMUM_VOLUME</primary><secondary>Options.h</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Options.h</primary><secondary>MAXIMUM_VOLUME</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>constexpr uint8_t MAXIMUM_VOLUME = -1.0 / -0.5<computeroutput>[constexpr]</computeroutput></computeroutput></para>
<para>Maximum volume. This may be used to simply limit the volume. If 0, volume can go all the way to 0 dB, and once there, the Vol+ button on the remote won&apos;t wake up the display. </para>
</section>
